Source:  TrNZi
Author:
Vol / Page:  24/203
Edition:
Quote:  2. <i>Mokohinou islands</i>. - Hapuku (or groper), hiwihiwi, barracouta, maomao, spotty, parrot-fish, leather jacket, korokoro-pounamou. <i>ibid.</i> 24/215 Again, from Mokohinou Mr. Sandager records, in September, 1888, the capture of a fish which he calls `korokoro-pounamou.' The specimen weighed 6lb., and contained Medusae in the stomach. i do not know what fish is referred to.
